The paper deals with the concept of tractability and complexity classes, which are central topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the construction of algorithms and heuristics for decision problems, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the generation of random instances for decision problems, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
